<br>
The monthly fee is $12.95 base if I recall correctly. You can reduce is somewhat by going for longer subscription times as in EQ. E.G. For a 3 month subscription the fee drops to an equivalent $11.95 a month.<br>
<br>
Buying and selling in DAoC doesn't really equate to the EQ market. Why? For two reasons (IMO) really. First is the con system for equipment. Higher level equipment degrades faster and the bonuses *appear* to be capped. This prevents your friends from dropping uber weapons on a low level character and have said lowbie decimate any level appropriate hunting grounds.<br>
<br>
The second thing is that player made items (as a general rule) are superior to mob drops. So what seems to happen (in my experience) is that a person crafts an item for themselves or they hire someone to craft a piece or set of armor, or a weapon, etc.<br>
<br>
Since items degrade over time, even if you had a nice weapon or suit of armor, after you have used it for extended periods and either had it repaired or repaired it yourself, the armor is not as effective as a new suit of amor/weapon.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, tradeskills are actually quite useful in DAoC for the above mentioned reasons.<br>
<br>
Hope that answers your questions. <p>Jerit  Albion Mercenary<BR>
